Node binds to `0.0.0.0` unless a host is specified. On a multi-tenant or misconfigured host this means the service is reachable on any NIC. Port and host should come from env vars so deployment can control exposure.

**Fix:**
```js
const PORT = Number(process.env.PORT) || 3000;
const HOST = process.env.HOST || '127.0.0.1';
app.listen(PORT, HOST, () => console.log(`Server on ${HOST}:${PORT}`));
```

---

